oryx_path_planning::Tentacle::Tentacle ( double  exp_fact,
double  seed_rad,

int  num_tent,

int  x_dim,
int  y_dim,
double  velocity 
) throw (TentacleGenerationException)

Creates a new Tentacle using the given parameters for its construction.

Author:
Adam Panzica
Parameters:
exp_factThe exponential factor parameter used to calculate the radius of the tentacle
seed_radThe seed radius for the speed set the tentacle is in
seed_lengthThe seed length that was used to calculate the seed radius
indexThe tentacle index of this tentacle
num_tentThe total number of tentacles in the speed set
resolutionThe resolution of the occupancy grid that the tentacle will be overlaid on
x_dimThe length of the x-axis of the occupancy grid, in the positive x-direction and of the same units as resolution
y_dimThe length of the y-axis of the occupancy grid, in the positive y-direction and of the same units as resolution
velocityThe velocity that the tentacle is to be traveled at
Exceptions:
TentacleGenerationExceptionIf there is a problem generating the tentacle
